ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Absolutely. Everyone should take this class. The work and readings are both manageable and fascinating. The discussions are really interesting.

I would recommend this class if you truly are interested in architecture theory and in the topic of modern religious architecture. I found it interesting, although towards the end it got a little bit dry.I took this class as a non-architecture major freshman and did not feel too overwhelmed, so prior knowledge is not really necessary.
